Officers are investigating a potential homicide Saturday, according to the Tampa Police Department. Police said they found a deceased man in the driveway of a home in the 3600 block of N. 53rd St. in Tampa just after midnight, according to a media release. The body was found next to a pick-up truck. A second vehicle was left running and abandoned on the east side of N 53rd Street, which was later determined to be stolen, police said. The investigation is ongoing. This is a breaking news story. Stick with tampabay.com for updates.